}} The 1998-1999 FA Cup was won by Manchester United, who beat Newcastle United
2â0 in the final at the old Wembley Stadium. The goals were scored by Teddy
Sheringham after 11 minutes, less than two minutes after coming on as a
substitute for Roy Keane, and Paul Scholes on 53 minutes. It was the second leg
of an historic Treble for Manchester United; having already won the Premier
League title the previous weekend, they went on to win the UEFA Champions League
the following Wednesday.
